The paper discusses a software framework for conducting experiments on Quality of Experience (QoE) through the presentation of stimuli and collection of participant data. This suggests a focus on Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) and Multimedia (cs.MM) research. The use of questionnaires also suggests a potential focus on Information Retrieval (cs.IR) and Social and Information Networks (cs.SI) research. Finally, the mention of multimedia content playback suggests a potential focus on Computational Linguistics (cs.CL) research.
